main event: A woman reported seeing a large, bright object with many green and blue lights over a field near Beech Corner, Idaho on November 16, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared oblong and similar to a large meteor, but the witness did not think it was a meteor.
The object glided down to about 30 feet off the ground as it passed the highway.
The object was self-luminous, not reflecting any other light source.
The object was in view for only about 30 seconds.
The witness was driving alone at the time and does not know if anyone else observed the object.
sighted object: a large, bright object with many green and blue lights
witnesses: one civilian witness, a woman driving in her car
